<HEADLINE>
MANAGEMENT STAFF MAKES LESS THAN NT$50,000 PER MONTH: DGBAS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Jan. 1 (CNA) 01/01/07  19:34:21 (By Lilian Wu)
</P>
<P>
Management personnel in the industrial and service sectors on
average made less than NT$50,000 (US$1,525) per month in 2006,
according to the results of a survey released Monday by the
Directorate General of Budget, Accounting and Statistics (DGBAS).
</P>
<P>
The Cabinet-level agency consistently conducts a job market
survey between May and June every year and publish the result at
the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The 2006 survey shows that employees in the industrial and
service sectors on average were receiving NT$26,266 per month at
the end of May 2006, up slightly from the NT$26,074 in a survey
in June 2005.
</P>
<P>
Supervising staff in the two sectors had the highest average
salaries of NT$47,630 per month, followed by professionals at
NT$35,899. Non-technical or laborers had the lowest average
monthly salary at around NT$20,000.
</P>
<P>
Monthly salaries for executives in supervisory positions fell
below NT$50,000, down NT$2,839 from the previous survey of
NT$50,469 in June  2005.
</P>
<P>
Salaries for technical staff or assistant professionals also
decreased by NT$2,819, while those of general affairs staff
increased by NT$2,348, and service sector workers and the
salesmen increased by NT$2,133.
</P>
<P>
The survey also found that labor shortages in the industrial and
service sectors numbered 161,000 in June 2006, up 5,000 from June
2005. Among them, the labor shortage in the industrial sector was
95,000 and the labor shortage in the service sector was 66,000.
</P>
<P>
By trade, the manufacturing sector was short of 81,986 workers,
followed by wholesale and retail at 29,665 and the construction
sector at 12,767.
</P>
<P>
The survey also found that the labor shortage at the Hsinchu
Science Park increased significantly to 5,932 in May 2006, up
2,255 from the previous survey. The average salary of the park
was NT$32,895, up NT$6,000 from the previous survey.
</P>
